      • getCollectCode

        public CollectCode getCollectCode()
        Returns the value of field 'collectCode'. The field 'collectCode' has the following description: [Optional] This parameter allows the application to request that a DTMF tone detector (TN744) be connected to the routed call and to detect and collect caller (call originator) entered code/digits. The collectCode and userProvidedCode are mutually exclusive. If collectCode is present, then userProvidedCode cannot be present.
        Returns:
        CollectCode

      • getDestRoute

        public DeviceID getDestRoute()
        Returns the value of field 'destRoute'. The field 'destRoute' has the following description: [Optional] Specifies the TAC/ARS/AAR information for off-PBX destinations, if the information is not included in the routeSelected. A NULL parameter specifies no TAC/ARS/AAR information.
        Returns:
        DeviceID

      • getDirectAgentCallSplit

        public DeviceID getDirectAgentCallSplit()
        Returns the value of field 'directAgentCallSplit'. The field 'directAgentCallSplit' has the following description: [Optional] Specifies the ACD agent's split extension for a Direct-Agent call routing. A Direct-Agent call is a special type of ACD call that is directed to a specific agent rather than to any available agent. The agent specified in the routeSelected must be logged into the split. A NULL parameter specifies that this is not a Direct-Agent call.
        Returns:
        DeviceID

      • getNetworkCallRedirection

        public java.lang.Short getNetworkCallRedirection()
        Returns the value of field 'networkCallRedirection'. The field 'networkCallRedirection' has the following description: [Optional] Specifies whether or not NetworkCallRedirection (NCR) should be invoked. Values are "On" (1) or "Off" (0). When "On" is selected, the routeSelected service parameter specifies a PSTN routing number (without an access code) for NCR requests. If the parameter is not specified, then the value defaults to "Off".
        Returns:
        Short

      • getPriorityCalling

        public java.lang.Boolean getPriorityCalling()
        Returns the value of field 'priorityCalling'. The field 'priorityCalling' has the following description: [Optional] Specifies the priority of the call. Values are "On"(TRUE) or "Off" (FALSE). When "On" is selected, a priority call is placed if the routeSelected is an on-PBX destination. When "On" is selected for an off-PBX calledDevice, the call will be denied.
        Returns:
        Boolean

        Returns the value of field 'userData'.
        Returns:

      • getUserProvidedCode

        public UserProvidedCode getUserProvidedCode()
        Returns the value of field 'userProvidedCode'. The field 'userProvidedCode' has the following description: [Optional] This parameter allows the application to send code/digits (ASCII string with 0-9, *, and # only) with the routed call. These code/digits are treated as dial-ahead digits for the call, and are stored in a dial-ahead digit buffer. The userProvidedCode and collectCode are mutually exclusive. If userProvidedCode is present, then collectCode cannot be present.
        Returns:
        UserProvidedCode
